  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through multiple approaches, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Advanced data tracking and digital evidence gathering\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n\n4. Regulatory Frameworks\n- Financial crime compliance programs\n- Strict penalties for non-compliance\n- Regular audits and monitoring\n\n5. Technological Solutions\n- Advanced transaction monitoring systems\n- Artificial intelligence and machine learning detection\n- Blockchain tracking mechanisms\n\nThese strategies aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and technological approaches.",
